Microservices and resilience.

What is covered.

This notebook covers the architectural style most large systems land in, and the resilience patterns that keep it standing. We start with the real trade-offs between a monolith and microservices, then walk through the gateway and service mesh that wire services together, the saga pattern for transactions that cross service boundaries, and the resilience trio — circuit breaker, bulkhead, and idempotent retries.
